settings.title: Bachelor & Bachelorette Parties
settings.text: Check out our special promotion for Bachelor Parties in Las Vegas. Our BOOM FOR THE GROOM promotion offers 5 rounds on .50 BMG Barrett M107A1 Sniper Rifle (Retail Value $99.95). Promotion Requirements: Group (including Bachelor) must purchase a minimum of 5 shooting packages or more (may be any combination). Bachelor then qualifies for our BOOM FOR THE GROOM promotion. Get complimentary round-trip transportation for your group. Flex your muscles, guys. Ever considered doing a co-ed Bachelor and Bachelorette party? Just an idea so you don't leave the ladies and her gal pals out. You may also book within the same reservation shooting packages for Bachelorettes. Just saying, she'll thank you later.

settings.title: Corporate Events
settings.text: Book your corporate group, executive outing or team building event at our indoor shooting range. A great way to reward your employees or top customers, build new relationships or simply say "thank you." Bring your employees or customers to the most upscale indoor shooting range in the world!

settings.title: Group Events
settings.text: Whether you're celebrating a birthday, divorce, engagement party or any other special occasion, book your large group at our indoor shooting range. Bring your group of 10+ shooters and come shoot at the Most Upscale Indoor Shooting Range in the World!

settings.question: Do I need a special permit, license, or experience to shoot at your gun range?
settings.answer: No experience, permit, or license is required. First time shooters are expertly instructed on firearm safety and technique by Strip Gun Club's NRA certified staff. Government issued photo identification must be presented to shoot. This includes a valid Driver's License or Passport as sufficient documentation.

settings.question: Do I need to make a reservation?
settings.answer: Reservations are not required, but are recommended. You may easily self-book your Shooting Package(s) online 24/7. You may add-on additional shooting packages and ammunition upon arrival. You may also book reservations for groups of 10+ or more shooters. Please visit our Events page for details.

settings.question: How do I make a reservation?
settings.answer: Simply self-book online anytime. You will automatically receive a reservation confirmation and receipt via email. If you require assistance booking please contact us or call us during normal business hours at 702-777-GUNS.

settings.question: How do I know which package to pick?
settings.answer: Our expert staff can assist you in selecting a package that is just right for you. Contact us at info@stripgunclub.com, call 702-777-GUNS or select your package in person with our assistance when you arrive.

settings.question: What is the best way to get to Strip Gun Club?
settings.answer: Strip Gun Club is conveniently located on the Las Vegas Strip close to most Strip casinos including The Strat and The Sahara, and just four miles from McCarran International Airport. Click here for directions.

settings.question: What would prohibit me from shooting at Strip Gun Club?
settings.answer:
Shooter Eligibility Conditions: Upon arrival all guests must present a government issued form of identification such as a passport, driver license or US issued military id card. Any individual or group member meeting any of the below listed conditions will be prohibited from participating in shooting activities, and in certain cases may be legally prohibited from being present on the premises. Persons legally prohibited from possessing or handling firearms that falsely endorse our Indemnity Waiver and proceed with shooting activities may be subject to criminal charges. Individuals or group members may not be:

- Convicted of or under indictment for a crime punishable by imprisonment exceeding one year (felony) and/or convicted of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.

- Subject to a court order restraining them for harassing, stalking, or threatening their child, intimate partner or child of an intimate partner.

- A fugitive from justice.

- Dishonorably discharged from the Armed Forces.

- Adjudicated mentally defective or have been involuntarily committed to a mental institution.

- Under the influence of drugs and/or alcohol.

- In possession of medical or recreational marijuana.

- A medical marijuana permit holder.

- A patron of a marijuana dispensary.

- Pregnant

- A minor under the age of 18 unaccompanied by a parent or legal guardian.

- A minor under the age of 10.

- Non-compliant with Strip Gun Club safety rules & regulations.

settings.question: What days is Strip Gun Club open?
settings.answer: Everyday except Thanksgiving (US), Christmas Eve and Christmas Day.

settings.question: How old do you have to be to shoot?
settings.answer: Eighteen years old unaccompanied, or ten years old when accompanied by a parent or legal guardian. Firearms selection for minors is at the discretion of our staff.

settings.text:
Welcome to Strip Gun Club

The only luxury shooting range located on the Las Vegas Strip. We offer a wide selection of guns. Including pistols, shotguns, sniper rifles, submachine guns and home to the world's largest Fully Automatic 50 BMG Belt Fed machine gun. View our selection of firearms and book your next shooting experience with us today!

How to find us

Set your sights on the Strips one and only shooting range. Were right at the corner of Sahara and Las Vegas Boulevard, close to most Strip casinos, including the Strat and The Sahara, so you can go from high stakes to high velocity in a heartbeat.
